# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
**Modified:** `package.json`
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights` version ^2.0.0 to dependencies
- Package manager (pnpm) automatically updated `pnpm-lock.yaml`

### 2. Component Integration
**Already Configured:** `app/layout.tsx`
- The SpeedInsights component was already imported and integrated in the root layout
- Import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next"`
- Component placed at the end of the body tag: `<SpeedInsights />`
- This follows the official Next.js App Router (v13.5+) installation pattern

### 3. Build Verification
**Status:** ✅ SUCCESSFUL
- Ran `pnpm install` to install the new package
- Ran `pnpm run build` to verify the production build completes successfully
- Build completed without errors in 4.4s using Next.js 16.2.0 (Turbopack)
- All routes compiled and generated successfully (/, /_not-found, /contact)

## Implementation Notes

### Framework Detection
This is a Next.js 16.2.0 project using the App Router architecture, confirmed by:
- Presence of `app/layout.tsx` (not `pages/_app.tsx`)
- Next.js version 16.2.0 in package.json
- Modern React 19 with Server Components

### Installation Approach
Following the official Vercel documentation, the implementation uses:
- Package: `@vercel/speed-insights` 
- Import path: `@vercel/speed-insights/next` (Next.js-specific)
- Component: `<SpeedInsights />` (no props required for basic setup)
- Placement: End of `<body>` tag in root layout alongside existing Analytics component

### Package Manager
Detected pnpm as the package manager based on:
- Presence of `pnpm-lock.yaml` (133KB)
- Used `pnpm add` for installation
- Lockfile properly updated and committed

## Testing Results

✅ Package installation completed successfully
✅ Build verification passed (production build successful)
✅ No TypeScript errors
✅ All routes generated successfully
✅ Lockfile updated correctly

## Next Steps

Speed Insights is now fully configured and will:
1. Automatically track Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS, FCP, TTFB)
2. Send performance metrics to Vercel when deployed
3. Work seamlessly in production without additional configuration

The Speed Insights data will be visible in the Vercel dashboard after deployment at:
https://vercel.com/[your-project]/analytics/speed-insights
